Hands-down, the very best pizza I have eaten. There is a degree of perfection here in the quality of the crust and how it elevates the perfect amount of toppings. I have eaten a LOT of gourmet pizza. Without doubt, this crust is the zenith, the Apex, the very height of what pizza crust should be. The salads were also excellent. The service was great, happy and attentive. However, she could have known the craft beer list a bit better. She advertised as "local" some beers made in Michigan. But, perhaps not a beer-drinker herself, she was substituting "craft" for "local". At any rate, this is no biggie. However, they have two seating areas, one is upstairs, inside, and tiny. The other is a patio that can be enclosed with vinyl walls and heated. We arrived too late for the upper room and we're relegated to the patio...where the walls were not zipped together and the cold wind blew right through. The heater was no match. Once the large table that apparently liked it that way left, walls were zipped and comfort level went up. So go here in warmer weather for a truly five-star pizza experience. So dang good!

Cozy upstairs dining room that has windows overlooking Seaton Place.  Nice music playing, service is attentive, while not overwhelming.   Menu is self-explanatory, but the server didn't try to upsell an appetizer or salad.  The crust was a little thick for my liking for Hand-tossed  (I can get my own dough thinner).  Sauce had just the right amount of sweetness.  The cheese had the wonderful addition of milky buffalo which gave the mozzarella a little heft and a lot of chew.  Toppings were fresh, and the onions were delightfully tender and mild.  The sausage tasted of fennel and oregano, and I longed for more of it to nibble.  Overall a nice pizza, a nice drink and a really pleasant place to dine.
